{"GUID":"2f2a7316-58fe-4b16-ba1f-1a8b9b1bbf6a","Type":"Text","Text":"Contact Joel Christner joel.christner@gmail.com Founder at View www.linkedin.com/in/joelchristner El Dorado Hills, California, United States (LinkedIn) www.joelchristner.com (Personal) scholar.google.com/citations Summary (Portfolio) Building businesses - built successful businesses to maturity or exit nuget.org/profiles/jchristn (Portfolio) while establishing recognized leadership positions
Top Skills Product, technology, and solution architecture - understanding Storage Architecture complex problems, building creative solutions to address market and Software Development customer requirements Data Center
Product management and technical marketing - definition, Publications requirements, specifications, use-case centric direction and focus, Deploying Cisco Wide Area technical leadership for large distributed teams, creating relevant and Application Services high-impact business and technical content
Patents Competitive and market analysis - dismantling and exposing System and method for identifying competitors, identifying strengths, enabling sales to win, determining access patterns short and long-term trends and how to best capitalize Probabilistic model for file-specific compression selection under sla- constraints Polished and diverse communication skills - any size audience, any Probabilistic Model for File-Specific place in the organizational chart Compression Selection under SLA Constraints Blockchain-as-a-service integrated Skilled developer and architect - open source developer with an hybrid object storage system in interest in information search and retrieval, storage, messaging, API multi-cloud computing environment infrastructure, and distributed systems Access control rights assignment capabilities utilizing a new context- based hierarchy of data based on Published author - three technology-centric books, numerous new forms of metadata articles, whitepapers, and other material
Homepage: http://www.joelchristner.com Github: https://github.com/jchristn Nuget: https://www.nuget.org/profiles/jchristn Google Scholar: https://scholar.google.com/citations? user=Yg_E8dcAAAAJ&hl=en
Experience Page 1 of 5
View Founder April 2024 - Present (3 months)
View.io provides a data-as-a-service (DaaS) platform that automatically prepares and connects your data with AI apps and infrastructure, offering the keys to unlock the full potential of your data assets.
Pioneer Fund Venture Partner, Pioneer Fund November 2021 - Present (2 years 8 months)
Fundamental Ventures Limited Partner November 2022 - Present (1 year 8 months) Austin, Texas, United States
.NET Foundation Member April 2023 - Present (1 year 3 months)
Contributed and licensed multiple projects to the .NET Foundation to help bolster the developer ecosystem in C#; focus areas are in the realm of distributed systems, web services, messaging, and data management.
SNIA 2 years 1 month
Chair, DNA Data Storage CODEC Workgroup October 2023 - April 2024 (7 months)
Led a team defining standard CODECs and its attributes for use with DNA as a data storage media type.
Chair, DNA Data Storage Rosetta Stone Workgroup April 2022 - April 2024 (2 years 1 month)
Led a team that defined the first two specifications for consuming an archive of data stored on DNA as a storage media type.
Dell Technologies Distinguished Engineer, Director March 2019 - April 2024 (5 years 2 months) San Francisco Bay Area
Page 2 of 5
Office of the CTO, Research; focus areas include artificial intelligence, next- generation storage interfaces and media types, data management, as-a- service architectures, and distributed systems.
CloudGenix (acquired by Palo Alto Networks) Vice President, Marketing June 2017 - March 2019 (1 year 10 months) San Jose, CA
Led all aspects of marketing (web, brand identity, marketing funnels, GTM strategy) and developer experience (messaging, documentation, SDKs).
CAKE Corporation (Acquired by Sysco Foods) Chief Architect January 2015 - June 2017 (2 years 6 months) Redwood City, CA
Designed and built the back-end card processing and ACH settlement engine supporting thousands of merchants of various sizes and annual payment volume measured in tens of billions USD.
Cube (Acquired by Rocket Lawyer) Co-founder and Chief Technology Officer January 2012 - October 2014 (2 years 10 months) Mountain View, CA
Founded and led technology strategy and implementation for one of the market's first in-person point of sale, card terminal, and developer payments API platforms. Acquired thousands of merchants and over 100 developer partners prior to acquisition.
StorSimple Inc. (Acquired by Microsoft) Chief Scientist August 2009 - January 2012 (2 years 6 months) Santa Clara, CA
Responsible for overall system architecture for category-defining cloud storage controller, including product management, marketing, collateral, design, and architecture.
Cisco Systems, Inc. Technical Leader August 2008 - August 2009 (1 year 1 month) San Jose, CA
Page 3 of 5
Led overall cross-product architecture for WAN optimization spanning branch and data center platforms (routing, switching, compute), integrated modules, and standalone appliances.
Reconnex Corporation (Acquired by McAfee) Director, Product Management July 2007 - August 2008 (1 year 2 months) Mountain View, CA
Responsible for a suite of category-defining data loss prevention (DLP) products including marketing, product management, brand identity, content, collateral, and both system and solution architecture. Led the company to a market leadership position with multiple analysts and grew revenue over 250%.
Cisco Systems, Inc. Manager, Technical Marketing December 2002 - July 2007 (4 years 8 months) San Jose, CA
Led technical marketing for a family of category-defining application delivery products including WAN optimization and application acceleration. Responsible for content, collateral, positioning, competitive intelligence and analysis, product management, collaboration with beta customers, and engineering leadership.
Levi, Ray, and Shoup, Inc. Network Consultant June 1998 - December 2001 (3 years 7 months) Springfield, IL
Helped dozens of customers in the midwest, from small-medium business to government (state, local), large enterprise (financial, insurance, retail), on network and system architecture for a variety of technologies including client and server operating systems and applications, networking, security, data center, and data storage.
Education
Columbia University - Fu Foundation School of Engineering and Applied Science Master of Science, Computer Science · (2007 - 2010)
Page 4 of 5
Y Combinator · (2011 - 2012)
